'''''Pinball''''' is a pinball simulation written by John Allen and published by Acorn Software Products in 1980 for the [[TRS-80]].<ref name="after40"/><ref name="giantlist">{{cite web |last1=Hague |first1=James |title=The Giant List of Classic Game Programmers |url=https://dadgum.com/giantlist/}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
[[File:Pinball - 1980 video game.png|thumb|Gameplay screenshot]]
''Pinball'' is a game which gives variable speed of the ball as well as variable power of the ball release.<ref name="SG"/>

==Reception==
Jon Mishcon reviewed ''Pinball'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 36.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal|last=Mishcon |first=Jon |date=February 1981 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=36|pages=27}}</ref> Mishcon commented that "As a program, a strong endorsement, as a game, a qualified yes."<ref name="SG"/>

